npx --no -- commitlint --edit "$1" || {
  cat <<'EOF'

Commit messages need a conventional subject plus a useful body.

Use the body to explain:
- why the change was needed
- what changed at the behavioral or architectural level
- what validation was run, or why it was not run

Example:
fix(account): preserve reward claim denial reason

Reward claim responses include a machine-readable denial reason when
the user cannot claim Spark. Preserve it in the public account reward
shape so consumers can explain disabled claim states correctly.

Validation: npm run build
EOF
  exit 1
}
